<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="232" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,835,1113]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,835,861]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">Remarks.</emphasis>
This family of sessile crinoids displays a morphological and functional convergence with barnacles. The aboral cup restricted to the radial circlet is fixed to the substrate by an incrusting base with parallel growth lines more or less developed. The relatively short arms curl inwards and retract into the calcinal cavity with the proximal brachials forming a protective roof at rest. Study of extant species (
<bibRefCitation author="Ameziane, N. &amp; Bourseau, J. - P. &amp; Heinzeller, T. &amp; Roux, M." box="[918,1164,943,969]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" pagination="139 - 170" refId="ref25188" refString="Ameziane, N., Bourseau, J. - P., Heinzeller, T. &amp; Roux, M. (1999) Les genres Cyathidium et Holopus au sein des Cyrtocrinida (Crinoidea: Echinodermata). Journal of Natural History, 33, 139 - 170. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 002229399300335" type="journal article" year="1999">
Améziane 
<emphasis box="[1042,1092,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">et al</emphasis>
. 1999
</bibRefCitation>
) has clarified the major characters that distinguish 
<taxonomicName authorityName="d'Orbigny" authorityYear="1837" box="[459,554,979,1005]" class="Crinoidea" family="Holopodidae" genus="Holopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyrtocrinida" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[459,554,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">Holopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Steenstrup, 1847" authorityName="Steenstrup" authorityYear="1847" box="[613,744,979,1005]" class="Crinoidea" family="Holopodidae" genus="Cyathidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cyrtocrinida" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[613,744,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">Cyathidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the only two known extant genera attributed to this family (
<tableCitation box="[159,260,1015,1041]" captionStart="TABLE 17" captionStartId="31.[151,239,1160,1184]" captionText="TABLE 17. Main characters differentiating the genera Cyathidium and Holopus." pageId="31" pageNumber="232">Table 17</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,835,1113]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,538,1050,1076]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">Stratigraphical distribution.</emphasis>
Late Cretaceous (Cenomanian)–Recent, possibly since Late Jurassic (Sieverts-Doreck 1951).
</paragraph>
